text: We're raised to aspire to fame and fortune, when it seems like access and opportunity are far more valuable.

Weather and traffic
conspire to remind us
we're not in control.
I'm letting some old unused domain names go - you can have larrypages.com, nevarforget.us or IsHavingAMassage.com if you promise to use 'em!
Is The-Dream the first SEO-optimized pop singer? I think so. http://icanhaz.com/the-dream
Writing reference letters for friends is fun because it's kind of like giving a wedding toast on paper.
After half a decade, I'm ready to concede: Speakerboxx is a better album than The Love Below.
It's a pleasant mix of familiarity and disorientation to be a tourist in a neighborhood where I used to live.
@kevinrose Only speaking through FB and Twitter means you're mostly preaching to the choir. What about those you aren't yet connected to?
Since today is St. Patrick's Day, you can all call me "O'neill Dash".
Won't you all join me in celebrating the 20th anniversary of the release of Milli Vanilli's debut album?
How long until karaoke bars start advertising that they've got autotune? Anybody seen that on a sign yet?
@ToureX jay won, but we got "ether" as a verb out of it, so really we writers won.
@jimmyfallon has me & @garyvee onscreen for 2 seconds tonight, right after @rustyrockets and right before @kevinrose and @alexalbrecht. Woo!
@qoolquest sorry to geek out about meeting you just now, but you are genuinely a superhero
Speaking of gadget blogs, I have an EXCLUSIVE of some awesome unboxing footage: http://icanhaz.com/unboxing
Which gadget blog will be the first to test the tiny new iPod shuffle's ability to function after passing through the human digestive tract?
@sparkcbc Thanks for having me on your show today!
My coworkers are telling me that I am getting punchy, but actually they just don't realize I'm fucking hysterically funny all the time.
Predictable -- @deadspin makes a nice reference to my blog; commenters note that "Anil" looks like "anal": http://deadspin.com/5166953
@themediaisdying outs himself with an interesting Businessweek piece: http://bit.ly/mediadying
To those asking, I'm not going to any of the upcoming geek conferences (Etech, SXSW, MIX). Have fun without me!
Though I never watch USA, it's cool they honored folks like Charles, David and Jimmy: http://www.usanetwork.com/characterapproved/
Really happy that after 4 years of hearing about it, I can finally see Nina Paley's Sita Sings the Blues: http://www.sitasingstheblues.com/
Played Mario Kart for the first time in ages & confirmed I'm still awesome at it. In this economy, it's important to keep your skills sharp.
Apparently, my book review exclaiming "It's like a 200-page Wikipedia article!" is not considered a ringing endorsement by some people.
The other day @samruby wrote one of my favorite blog posts so far this year: http://tinyurl.com/ao6rhe
We took thousands of photos on our trip to India, and this is one of my absolute faves: http://www.flickr.com/photos/anildash/3293973690/
Playing around with Amazon Kindle on my iPod touch -- exactly the app I wanted. http://bit.ly/KlQTh

China's got a probe on the moon! That is awesome because I love the moon. Nice work, China.
